  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a plastic scale model of an **ultracentrifuge for uranium enrichment**, made at the **FOM Laboratory for Mass Spectrography** (later AMOLF) in Amsterdam in 1957. It represents the foundational technology of the **Dutch ultracentrifuge program**, which led to the establishment of **URENCO** — one of the world's largest commercial uranium enrichment companies — via the Treaty of Almelo (1970) with the UK and Germany. The model was designed by **Jacob Kistemaker** (1917–2010), the physicist who founded the Dutch enrichment program and who was simultaneously **conservator (curator) of Teylers' Natuurkundig Kabinet** (Physics Cabinet). The technology descended from this program was infamously stolen by **A.Q. Khan** in 1972–1975 and proliferated to Pakistan, Iran, Libya, and North Korea.",
